{
  "Context": "[1] «{'snippet': 'Mid-summer MLB baseball game . For the list of all - star games , see List of Major League Baseball All - Star Games .Since 2021, the Major League Baseball Draft has been held during the All - Star Break and in the host city of the All - Star Game .[47].', 'title': 'Major League Baseball All - Star Game - Wikipedia', 'link': 'https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Major_League_Baseball_All-Star_Game'}»\n[2] «{'snippet': 'Although the All - Star Game called for the defending Cup champion to host it, the game was held in Chicago Stadium in its second year as a consequence of the negotiations that set up the first game.', 'title': 'NHL All-Star Game - Wikipedia', 'link': 'https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/NHL_All-Star_Game'}»\n[3] «{'snippet': 'Rogers Centre (originally SkyDome) is a retractable roof stadium in downtown Toronto , Ontario, Canada, situated at the base of the CN Tower near the northern shore of Lake Ontario. Opened in 1989 on the former Railway Lands, it is home to the Toronto Blue Jays of Major League Baseball (MLB). List of Major League Baseball All - Star Game broadcasters The following is a list of the American radio and television networks and announcers that have broadcast the Major League Baseball All - Star Game over the years. From 1935 through 1944 and in 1946, the manager of each All-Star squad selected the entire team; in 1945, no MLB All - Star Game was held, and no All-Stars were officially named. Although the All - Star Game called for the defending Cup champion to host it, the game was held in Chicago Stadium in its second year as a consequence of the negotiations that set up the first game.', 'title': 'Rogers Centre - Wikipedia List of Major League Baseball All-Star Game broadcasters Major League Baseball All-Star Game - Wikipedia NHL All-Star Game - Wikipedia', 'link': 'https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Rogers_Centre'}»\n[4] «{'snippet': 'This decision was made following the announcement of Miami as host for the 2017 All - Star Game , which was the third consecutive year in which the game was hosted in an NL ballpark.', 'title': 'List of Major League Baseball All-Star Games - Wikipedia', 'link': 'https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/List_of_Major_League_Baseball_All-Star_Games'}»\n[5] «2016 American League Wild Card Game , the Toronto Blue Jays and the Baltimore Orioles. As both teams finished with identical 89–73 records, a tiebreaker was used to determine the host team. In accordance with MLB tiebreaking rules, the Blue Jays earned the right to host the game by winning their season series against the Orioles 10–9.\nThe Blue Jays beat the Orioles, 5–2, in extra innings. This was the Orioles' last postseason appearance until 2023.»",
  "Question": "When did toronto host the mlb all-star game?",
  "Disambiguations": [
    "DQ 1: When did Toronto host the MLB All-Star Game for the first time?",
    "DA 1: 1991"
  ],
  "Answer": "Toronto hosted the MLB All-Star Game for the first time in 1991. The game was held at the Rogers Centre, which was originally known as SkyDome. Rogers Centre is a retractable roof stadium in downtown Toronto, Ontario, Canada, situated at the base of the CN Tower near the northern shore of Lake Ontario."
