{
  "Context": "[1] «{'snippet': 'The final title comes from a soliloquy in Macbeth, in which the title character describes life as "a tale told by an idiot , full of sound and fury , signifying nothing". [10][11][12]', 'title': 'The Sound and the Fury - Wikipedia', 'link': 'https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/The_Sound_and_the_Fury'}»
[2] «{'snippet': 'It is a tale Told by an idiot , full of sound and fury Signifying nothing.', 'title': 'Dorothea Tieck - Wikipedia', 'link': 'https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Dorothea_Tieck'}»
[3] «{'snippet': 'Faulkner's allusions to earlier authors are evidenced by his titles; the title of The Sound and the Fury comes from Macbeth's soliloquy: "it is a tale / Told by an idiot , full of sound and fury ,/ Signifying nothing."', 'title': 'William Faulkner - Wikipedia', 'link': 'https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/William_Faulkner'}»
[4] «{'snippet': 'It is a tale told by an idiot , full of sound and fury . Signifying nothing. L.', 'title': 'Category:Shakespearean phrases - Wikipedia', 'link': 'https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Category:Shakespearean_phrases'}»
[5] «{'snippet': 'And tell me: is that story, sung by mystics and sages the world over, any crazier than the scientific materialism story, which is that the entire sequence is a tale told by an idiot , full of sound and fury , signifying absolutely nothing?', 'title': 'Ken Wilber - Wikipedia', 'link': 'https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Ken_Wilber'}»",
  "Question": "Who said it is a tale told by an idiot full of sound and fury?",
  "Disambiguations": "DQ 1: Who originally wrote the phrase "a tale told by an idiot, full of sound and fury"?;
DA 1: William Shakespeare
DQ 2: Which character said the phrase "a tale told by an idiot, full of sound and fury"?;
DA 2: Macbeth
DQ 3: Which Shakespeare character said the phrase "a tale told by an idiot, full of sound and fury"?;
DA 3: Macbeth
DQ 4: What play contains the phrase "a tale told by an idiot, full of sound and fury"?;
DA 4: Macbeth
DQ 5: Who said "it is a tale told by an idiot, full of sound and fury" in Shakespeare's Macbeth?;
DA 5: Macbeth
DQ 6: Who is the character that said "it is a tale told by an idiot, full of sound and fury" in Shakespeare's Macbeth?;
DA 6: Macbeth",
  "Answer": "The quote "a tale told by an idiot, full of sound and fury, signifying nothing" is from William Shakespeare's play Macbeth. The character Macbeth speaks this line in Act 5, Scene 5. Therefore, the character who said the quote is Macbeth. The phrase is also the namesake of William Faulkner's novel, *The Sound and the Fury.*"
}

{
  "Context": "[1] «{'snippet': 'During the Ottawa concert, Twain was joined by Lindsay Ell to perform \" (If You\'re Not in It for Love) I\'m Outta Here!\". \"Party for Two\" was performed with Breland on July 8–15, September 16–20, September 25–28, and October 7.', 'title': 'Queen of Me Tour - Wikipedia', 'link': 'https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Queen_of_Me_Tour'}»\n[2] «Queen of Me Tour , in support of her sixth studio album Queen of Me (2023). The tour began on April 28, 2023, in Spokane, Washington, and concluded in Vancouver, Canada on November 14, 2023. It marks the singer's first tour in nearly five years, following a highly successful Vegas residency run, Let's Go! which ran from 2019 through 2022.»\n[3] «Now Tour (Shania Twain) , in support of her fifth studio album Now (2017). The tour began on May 3, 2018, in Tacoma, and was initially scheduled to conclude in Las Vegas on August 4, 2018 but was later extended to conclude in Dunedin on December 22, 2018. The tour marks Twain's first since 2015's Rock This Country Tour, which, at the time, Twain announced would be her final run out on the road.»\n[4] «{'snippet': 'Shania : Still the One was a first concert residency by Canadian singer-songwriter Shania Twain , performed at The Colosseum at Caesars Palace in Las Vegas, Nevada. The show began on December 1, 2012, and ended on December 13, 2014, with Twain performing more than 100 times.', 'title': 'Shania : Still the One - Wikipedia', 'link': 'https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Shania:_Still_the_One'}»\n[5] «{'snippet': \"Following the release of the song, he announced that his first album, Lord of the Flies & Birds & Bees would be released on October 20, 2023. In October 2023, he was the opening act for three shows during Shania Twain 's 2023 Queen of Me Tour.\", 'title': 'Talk (musician) - Wikipedia', 'link': 'https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Talk_(musician)'}»",
  "Question": "Who is opening for shania twain in ottawa?",
