}

{
  "Context": "[1] «{'snippet': \"Test for lipids : add ethanol to sample, then shake; add water to the solution, and shake again.Lucas' reagent is used to distinguish between primary, secondary and tertiary alcohols. The bromine test is used to test for the presence of unsaturation and phenols.\", 'title': 'Chemical test - Wikipedia', 'link': 'https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Chemical_test'}»\n[2] «{'snippet': 'The emulsion test is a simple method used in educational settings to determine the presence of lipids using wet chemistry. The procedure is for the sample to be suspended in ethanol, allowing lipids present to dissolve ( lipids are soluble in alcohols).', 'title': 'Emulsion test - Wikipedia', 'link': 'https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Emulsion_test'}»\n[3] «{'snippet': 'This test is used to identify dyslipidemia (various disturbances of cholesterol and triglyceride levels), many forms of which are recognized risk factors for cardiovascular disease and rarely pancreatitis.', 'title': 'Lipid profile - Wikipedia', 'link': 'https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Lipid_profile'}»\n[4] «{'snippet': 'The Vertical Auto Profile (VAP) test is a blood analysis designed to accurately measure lipid and lipoprotein levels in the human body. [1]', 'title': 'Vertical auto profile - Wikipedia', 'link': 'https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Vertical_Auto_Profile'}»\n[5] «{'snippet': 'Lipids are a diverse and ubiquitous group of compounds which have many key biological functions, such as acting as structural components of cell membranes, serving as energy storage sources and participating in signaling pathways. Lipids may be broadly defined as hydrophobic or amphipathic small molecules that originate entirely or in part from two... See full list on en . wikipedia . org Lipid extraction Most methods of lipid extraction and isolation from biological samples exploit the high solubility of hydrocarbon chains in organic solvents. Given the diversity in lipid classes, it is not possible to accommodate all classes with a common extraction method. The traditional Bligh/Dyer procedure uses chloroform/methanol-based protocols that include phase partitioning into the organic layer. However, several protocols now exist, with newer methods overcoming the shortcomings of older ones and s... Lipid separation The simplest method of lipid separation is the use of thin layer chromatography (TLC). Although not as sensitive as other methods of lipid detection, it offers a rapid and comprehensive screening tool prior to more sensitive and sophisticated techniques.Solid-phase extraction (SPE) chromatography is useful for rapid, preparative separation of crude lipid mixtures into different lipid classes. This involves the use of prepacked columns containing silica or other stationary phases to separate g... Lipid detection The progress of modern lipidomics has been greatly accelerated by the development of spectrometric methods in general and soft ionization techniques for mass spectrometry such as electrospray ionization (ESI), desorption electrospray ionization (DESI), and matrix-assisted laser desorption/ionization (MALDI)in particular. \\\"Soft\\\" ionizationdoes not cause extensive fragmentation, so that comprehensive detection of an entire range of lipids within a complex mixture can be correlated to experiment... See full list on en . wikipedia . org The high sensitivity of DESI in the lipid range makes it a powerful technique for the detection and mapping of lipids abundances within tissue specimens.Recent developments in MALDI methods have enabled direct detection of lipids in-situ. Abundant lipid-related ions are produced from the direct analysis of thin tissue slices when sequential spectra... See full list on en . wikipedia . org Lipid profiling is a targeted metabolomics platform that provides a comprehensive analysis of lipid species within a cell or tissue. Profiling based on electrospray ionization tandem mass spectrometry (ESI-MS/MS) is capable of providing quantitative data and is adaptable to high throughput analyses. The powerful approach of transgenics, namely dele... See full list on en . wikipedia . org A major challenge for lipidomics, in particular for MS-based approaches, lies in the computational and bioinformatic demands of handling the large amount of data that arise at various stages along the chain of information acquisition and processing. Chromatographic and MS data collection requires substantial efforts in spectral alignment and statis... See full list on en . wikipedia . org The Vertical Auto Profile (VAP) test is a blood analysis designed to accurately measure lipid and lipoprotein levels in the human body. [1] Sudan IV (C 24 H 20 N 4 O) is a lysochrome (fat-soluble dye) diazo dye used for the staining of lipids , triglycerides and lipoproteins on frozen paraffin sections.', 'title': 'Lipidomics - Wikipedia Vertical auto profile - Wikipedia Sudan IV - Wikipedia', 'link': 'https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Lipidomics'}",
  "Question": "What do you use to test for lipids?",
  "Disambiguations": {
    "DQ 1": "What is used to test for lipids using the emulsion test?",
    "DA 1": "Ethanol and water"
  },
  "Answer": "There are several methods and substances used to test for lipids, depending on the context. In educational settings, the emulsion test, which uses ethanol and water, is a simple method to identify lipids. Sudan IV dye can be used for staining lipids, triglycerides, and lipoproteins. The Vertical Auto Profile (VAP) test is a blood analysis designed to accurately measure lipid and lipoprotein levels."
}

{
  "Context": "[1] «{'snippet': \"Give Me a Home Among the Gumtrees is a popular Australian song written in 1974 by Wally Johnson and Bob Brown. History. It was originally performed as a satirical number in Johnson and Brown's comedy act at the Flying Trapeze Cafe in Fitzroy...\", 'title': 'Give Me a Home Among the Gumtrees - Wikipedia', 'link': 'https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Give_Me_a_Home_Among_the_Gumtrees'}»\n[2] «{'snippet': '^ Wally Johnson was co- writer of the celebrated Australian folk song Give Me A Home Among The Gumtrees .', 'title': 'Sharin Anderson - Wikipedia', 'link': 'https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Sharin_Anderson'}»\n[3] «{'snippet': 'Most Performed Australasian Country Work. \" Give Me a Home Among the Gumtrees \" (Robert Brown, Walter Johnson) by Captain Rock, Bullamakanka.', 'title': 'APRA Music Awards of 1985 - Wikipedia', 'link': 'https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/APRA_Music_Awards_of_1985'}»\n[4] «{'snippet': \"Forrester's music also appeared on the Larrikin Records 1996 composite album, Give Me a Home Among the Gum Trees , along with Australian country-folk icons Eric Bogle, Judy Small, The Bushwackers, and others.\", 'title': 'Gary Jeshel Forrester - Wikipedia', 'link': 'https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Gary_Jeshel_Forrester'}»\n[5] «{'snippet': 'Give Me a Home Among the Gumtrees . Goodbye Blinky Bill. N.', 'title': 'Category:John Williamson (singer) songs - Wikipedia', 'link': 'https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Category:John_Williamson_(singer)_songs'}»",
