  "Context": "[1] «{'snippet': 'Hello , My Twenties ! is a South Korean television series starring Han Ye-ri, Han Seung-yeon, Park Eun -bin, Ryu Hwa-young, Park Hye-su, Ji Woo and Choi Ara. It aired on JTBC from July 22, 2016 to October 7, 2017. Synopsis.', 'title': 'Hello , My Twenties ! - Wikipedia', 'link': 'https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Hello,_My_Twenties!'}»\n[2] «{'snippet': 'Ahn made his debut in theater through the play Realise Happiness.Bong Yoon- jae (cameo). Hello , My Twenties !', 'title': 'Ahn Woo-yeon - Wikipedia', 'link': 'https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Ahn_Woo-yeon'}»\n[3] «{'snippet': '2016. Knocking on the Door of Your Heart. Yeon Eun -hee. [10]. Chae's Movie Theater. Hello , My Twenties ! Yoo Eun - jae .', 'title': 'Ji Woo - Wikipedia', 'link': 'https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Ji_Woo'}»\n[4] «Hello, My Twenties! , My Twenties! (Korean: 청춘시대; Hanja: 青春時代; RR: Cheongchunsidae; MR: Ch'ŏngchunsidae; lit. Age of Youth) is a South Korean television series starring Han Ye-ri, Han Seung-yeon, Park Eun-bin, Ryu Hwa-young, Park Hye-su, Ji Woo and Choi Ara. It aired on JTBC from July 22, 2016 to October 7, 2017.»\n[5] «{'snippet': 'Ji Il-joo ... Ji Il-joo (Korean: 지일주; born November 7, 1985) is a South Korean actor. He is known for his role in the drama series Weightlifting Fairy Kim Bok-joo (2016–2017) and Hello , My Twenties ! (2016)', 'title': 'Ji Il-joo - Wikipedia', 'link': 'https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Ji_Il-joo'}»",
