{
  "Context": "[1] «{'snippet': \"Hathaway played the White Queen in Tim Burton 's 2010 adaptation of the fantasy novels Alice 's Adventures in Wonderland and Through the Looking - Glass alongside Helena Bonham Carter and Johnny Depp.\", 'title': 'Anne Hathaway - Wikipedia', 'link': 'https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Anne_Hathaway'}\»\n[2] «{'snippet': 'Some characters from Through the Looking Glass featured in a conflation of both books on BBC Television in 1960, [n 15] but the first British television adaptation of Through the Looking Glass was in 1973, featuring Sarah Sutton ( Alice ), Brenda Bruce ( White Queen ), Richard Pearson (White King), Judy Parfitt (Red Queen), Geoffrey Bayldon (White ...', 'title': 'Through the Looking-Glass - Wikipedia', 'link': 'https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Through_the_Looking-Glass'}\»\n[3] «{'snippet': \"Snowdrop is Dinah's white kitten and a character of Lewis Carroll's novel Through The Looking - Glass and What Alice Found There. Snowdrop , who assumes the role of the White Queen , appears in chapters I and XII.\", 'title': 'List of minor characters in the Alice series - Wikipedia', 'link': 'https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/List_of_minor_characters_in_the_Alice_series'}\»\n[4] «{'snippet': 'In 2016, Crouch played younger versions of characters, including Sophie Cookson \'s Pippa in The Huntsman: Winter\'s War, Anne Hathaway \'s White Queen in Alice Through the Looking Glass , Olivia Cooke \'s Elizabeth \"Lizzie\" Cree in The Limehouse Golem, [6] as well as Ellise Chappell \'s Jennifer Strange in the Sky One television film The Last ...', 'title': 'Amelia Crouch - Wikipedia', 'link': 'https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Amelia_Crouch'}\»\n[5] «White King (Through the Looking-Glass) , he is one of the earliest chesspieces that are introduced into the story.  Although he does not interact with Alice as much as the White Queen does, because Alice becomes a pawn on his side of the Chess-game, he is, on some levels, the most important character within the story at least as far as the game is concerned.  He is not to be confused with the King of Hearts from Alice's Adventures in Wonderland.»",
  "Question": "Who plays the white queen in alice through the looking glass?",
  "Disambiguations": {
    "DQ 1": "Who played the White Queen in the 1973 British television adaptation of Through the Looking Glass?",
    "DA 1": "Brenda Bruce"
  },
  "Answer": "The role of the White Queen in Alice Through the Looking Glass has been interpreted by several actors across different adaptations. In the 1973 British television adaptation of Through the Looking Glass, the White Queen was played by Brenda Bruce. In Tim Burton's 2010 adaptation of the fantasy novels Alice's Adventures in Wonderland and Through the Looking-Glass, Anne Hathaway played the White Queen."
}

