{
  "question": "Who came up with a cure for tuberculosis?",
  "disambiguations": [
    "DQ 1: Who discovered the bacteria that causes tuberculosis?\nDA 1: Robert Koch",
    "DQ 2: Who invented artificial pneumothorax for tuberculosis treatment?\nDA 2: Carlo Forlanini; Norman Bethune"
  ],
  "answer": "Robert Koch discovered the bacteria that causes tuberculosis. Koch also announced tuberculin as a remedy for tuberculosis in 1890, but it was not effective as a cure, but was later adapted as a screening test. Artificial pneumothorax, which involved artificially collapsing the diseased lung, was a radical new treatment for tuberculosis, invented by Carlo Forlanini and popularized by Norman Bethune."
}
